author: COMSOL
description: Impedance tubes are used for estimating the surface impedance of various samples, for example, a layer of porous material used for sound insulation. This model shows how the five material parameters of the Johnson–Champoux–Allard model can be estimated from the pressure at two measurement microphones. The model includes an initial study, which generates synthetic measurement data. Noise is added to the data before it is exported.
label: impedance_tube_parameter_estimation_data.mph
